<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
C-141  IMMUNE DISEASES: NEW DEVELOPMENTS IN TREATMENT DRUGS
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>C-141  IMMUNE DISEASES: NEW DEVELOPMENTS IN TREATMENT DRUGS</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>PAVAN HANDA</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY GOAL AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

This market report on advances in the treatment of immune diseases
is an attempt to provide the pharmaceutical and biotechnology
executive with a comprehensive assessment of the current state of
technical advances as well as the commercial and market potential
of the development programs currently underway at various companies
and institutions.<P>

<B>REASONS FOR DOING THE STUDY</B><P>

Immune diseases are represented in a substantial proportion of the
population, are often chronic, debilitating and life threatening
and currently have no cure.  Many immune diseases are rare in
occurrence and not well known.  This study was undertaken to
examine the developments in the understanding of the immune system
over the 1980-1990 period and present the most likely commercial
products emanating from this research.<P>

<B>CONTRIBUTION OF THE STUDY</B><P>

The information and analysis presented in this report on immune
diseases will be an important asset in decision-making for managers
involved in business development, marketing, market research,
product development, mergers and acquisitions, licensing,
investment banking and deal creation, business management, and
consultants to the pharmaceutical and biotechnology industry.  The
study provides a comprehensive analysis of the markets for drugs
for the treatment of immune diseases from currently available
treatment to the market potential of promising drugs under
development.<P>

<B>STUDY SCOPE AND FORMAT</B><P>

The scope of the study is worldwide and presents all major immune
diseases.  The summary section provides a description of immune
diseases, prevalence of patient population and worldwide market
size estimates as well as growth rates for the period 1991 to 2001.
The industry overview section presents the growing importance of
the treatment of immune diseases in terms of market size and growth
in comparison to the total worldwide and U.S. pharmaceutical
industry.  Key tables on worldwide and U.S. prevalence, market size
and growth estimates for treatment of each of the major immune
diseases is presented in this section to provide a quick overview
of existing size and market potential.<P>

The section on Government Regulations explains the process of
clinical drug development, the U.S. FDA expedited Drug Approval
Plan of 1989 and the U.S. FDA Orphan Drug Act of 1983.<P>

The market section is the heart of the report and provides a
detailed analysis of each immune disease, currently available
treatment, status of new drugs under clinical development, early
research and development of new treatment modalities, companies
leading in research and development of immune-based drugs as well
as companies currently having leadership positions in the present
form of treatment.  Throughout the market section, all this
information is incorporated in developing estimates of expected
approval time frames for new immune-based and other drugs under
clinical trials, and market size and growth projections for the
treatment of each of the major immune diseases over the period 1991
to 2001.<P>

The section on industry structure provides a discussion on the
impact of and projected market position of new immune-based drugs
in the treatment of immune diseases, current and future market
leaders in the treatment of immune diseases, marketing and drug
development relationships between young, promising biotechnology
companies and worldwide pharmaceutical companies.  Pricing and
manufacturing issues during the commercialization of new immune-
based drugs have also been presented.<P>

The section on company profiles provides important information on
those companies that lead the pharmaceutical and biotechnology
industry in the research and development of new immune-based drugs
in the treatment of immune diseases as well as information on those
companies that have leadership position in the currently available
treatment of immune diseases.<P>

Included in the Appendix section is a discussion on the workings of
the body's immune system as well as a description of the immune
system drugs derived from biotechnology which demonstrate
commercial significance.<P>

<B>METHODOLOGY AND INFORMATION SOURCES</B><P>

The information and analysis presented in this report are based on
an extensive survey of the biotechnology and pharmaceutical
industries as well as a detailed examination of published
literature and reports obtained from regulatory authorities,
medical research institutions, pharmaceutical trade associations,
and national and world health organizations.  Key information from
the business literature was used as a basis to conduct dialogue and
obtain expert opinion on commercial potential and market sizes from
industry professionals.<P>

<B>RELATED BCC WORK</B><P>

The author recommends the following BCC reports for additional
information on anti viral products, biotechnology products and
vaccine development:  C-057 R entitled "Antiviral Drugs and
Vaccines"; C-065 R entitled "Bioengineered Protein Drugs"; and C-
072 entitled "New Horizons in the Pharmaceutical Industry."<P>

