<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
GB-072R  BIOCOMPATIBLE MATERIALS FOR THE HUMAN BODY
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2> GB-072R  BIOCOMPATIBLE MATERIALS FOR THE HUMAN BODY</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>BARBARA BREINDEL</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY GOAL AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

The goals and objectives of this study, The Biocompatible
Materials Marketplace, are to provide the reader with a
comprehensive description and evaluation of this dynamic
marketplace so that its significance to the practice of modern
medicine is understood.  The report focuses on the major
materials now in use and the emerging trend towards advanced
materials natural products.  Particular emphasis in placed on
research and development activities which will provide the
products being introduced within the next decade.<P>


<B>REASONS FOR DOING STUDY</B><P>

When BCC last looked at this market in 1984, it was a smaller,
less extensive market relying on materials that were
commercially available to other industries.  Products were
developed quickly, and often on a make-shift basis, to answer
clinical needs.  Today, the industry has evolved into one that
has a strong commitment to research and development in order
to design the most effective and efficient products possible.
This has yielded a complex mix of products within all
therapeutic categories with no single biocompatible material
serving all applications.<P>

As a result of this growth and recent scientific discoveries,
many opportunities are emerging within this market, as well as
many uncertainties.  This new study focuses on identifying
these areas.<P>


<B>CONTRIBUTIONS OF THE STUDY AND FOR WHOM</B><P>

This study will supply information on these particular areas:<P>

      Structure of the present and future biocompatible
materials industry<P>

      Market size of the industry at present and through 1995<P>

      Major segments and major materials and their relative
market share<P>

      Major players, their market share and estimates of
their future market presence<P>

      Technological and research advances<P>

      The significance of the regulatory environment and its
impact on this industry<P>

      International developments impacting on potential
end-markets<P>

      Market dynamics<P>

     Corporate strategies<P>


<B>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B><P>

This study encompasses all present and potential biocompatible
materials.  It specifically excludes any materials or products
that may be used in medical applications that do not come into
contact with the human body or body fluids.  Readers
interested in materials used in other medical applications and
products should contact BCC.<P>

The biocompatible materials covered in detail in this report
include polymers, ceramics, metals, composites and natural
materials.  End-market segments under examination include
implants, tissue replacement materials, materials for drug
delivery systems, detoxicants/dialysis/separation/filtration
systems, biosensors, artificial organs and cosmetic and dental
materials.<P>

Specifically excluded from this study are the materials used
as fillers and time release agents in drugs and medical
devices such as syringes and needles.<P>


<B>METHODOLOGY</B><P>

To prepare this report, the BCC analyst utilized primary and
secondary research techniques, including use of BCC's
extensive library of medical and scientific literature.
Numerous interviews were conducted with scientists, market
participants, market observers and regulatory personnel. Once
these data were collected they were analyzed by experienced
BCC personnel to determine specific findings. These findings
and all market forecasts were correlated with industry experts
to confirm their validity.<P>

Since this is a complex, multi-discipline market the task of
forecasting was complicated.  All forecasts made by BCC in
this report are the result of our extensive analysis of this
market.  All of these forecasts represent the consensus
opinion of BCC personnel, industry participants and industry
observers.<P>

<B>RELATED BCC WORK CREDENTIALS</B><P>

The BCC analyst serving as Project Director on this report has
both technical and advanced marketing degrees and extensive
experience in the medical and pharmaceutical industries as
well as in other high technology markets. Among other BCC
studies the analyst has published are reports on bioengineered
protein drugs, genetic engineering, drug packaging, new drug
delivery systems, medical diagnostic equipment and the laser
industry.<P>




