<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
G-116R:  FIBER OPTICS SENSORS
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>G-116R:  FIBER OPTICS SENSORS
</H2>

<HR><P>


<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY OBJECTIVES</B><P>

This new Business Communications Co. (BCC) report provides a
technical and economic market analysis of the fiber optic sensor
industry.<P>

The principal objectives of this study are to:<P>

<LI>Investigate and discuss fiber optic sensor technologies, and
  applications<P>

<LI>Characterize and quantify the current and future U.S. and
  worldwide markets for fiber optic sensors, including:<P>
<UL>       - intrinsic and<BR>
       - extrinsic sensors</UL><P>

<LI>Identify and characterize the principal industry participants<P>

<LI>Provide an overview and characterize the end-use markets for
  fiber optic sensors, including:<P>

 <UL>- Industrial machinery<BR>
  - Metal working<BR>
  - Industrial processing--petroleum, chemical, plastics, etc.<BR>
  - In-Plant process control<BR>
  - Medicine<BR>
  - Military<BR>
  - Aerospace<BR>
  - Electrical power industry</UL><P>

This study provides a substantive overview of the overall sensor
industry in order to compare conventional sensors with fiber optic
sensors.<P>



<b>REASONS FOR CONDUCTING STUDY</B><P>

Business Communications Company initiated this study of the fiber
optic sensor industry in response to inquiries regarding this
market. This new study provides a thorough analysis of the
U.S./North American market, and provides a market analysis and
market projections worldwide. In addition, this report is a natural
follow-on for a number of other optics, electro-optics, and fiber
optics reports that have been published by BCC over the last few
years.<P>

The study also is timely because of the many changes occurring in
the fiber optics end-use industries, particularly in the
military/aerospace industries, and other industrial and commercial
industries. There is considerable potential for fiber optic
sensors, but the industry is fraught with problems that must be
understood in order to plan successful strategy for this industry.<P>


<b>CONTRIBUTION OF THIS STUDY</B><P>

This study comes at a critical time in the development of new fiber
optic sensors and new fiber and sensor applications that will
demand unique types of sensing environments. This timely BCC study
seeks to answer these questions, and to provide a cogent discussion
covering the reasons for its conclusions.<P>

Foreign companies, fiber optic sensors, and technologies are
discussed, and a worldwide market analysis is included for fiber
optic sensors.<P>

The report provides a thorough analysis of the current and
potential markets for fiber optic sensors--specifically, it:<P>

<UL> -    provides an assessment of relevant technologies<P>
  -    provides market projections for 1990, 1993, and 1998<P>
  -    characterizes existing and potential applications<P>
  -    discusses the major driving forces behind the development of
       the industry<P>
  -    identifies niches of specific promise<P>
  -    provides a thorough and representative list of companies and
       organizations involved in the test equipment industry and
       major end-users<P>
  -     provides brief company profiles<P></UL>


<b>METHODOLOGY AND INFORMATION SOURCES</B><P>

The information presented in this study was derived, in part, from
over 50 interviews with knowledgeable industry and government
sources. Due to the increasing worldwide nature and importance of
the industry, in addition to domestic sources, foreign sources were
contacted and worldwide information and specific market data are
included in this report. In addition, a thorough search of the
technical, trade, and government literature was conducted.<P>

Extensive BCC in-house resources were consulted and utilized where
appropriate. This study was conducted over a two and one half-month
period ending in January, 1994. Dollar market projections are given
in constant 1993 dollars unless otherwise noted.<P>


