<CENTER><H2>GROWING MARKETS FOR LASER MATERIALS AND COMPONENTS</H2>
<HR><P>
<I>MR. NICHOLSON</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY GOAL AND OBJECTIVES</B>

<P>This study analyzes the market for laser materials and
components in the United States and abroad.  The study's
primary goal is to give readers a clear understanding of where
this market currently stands and where it is heading. 
Detailed market forecasts are presented and important economic
trends are analyzed to give readers a broad knowledge of the
laser materials and components area.  The basic technology
involved in each of the products is also explained in order to
give readers a complete understanding of this complex and
rapidly changing market.  <P>


<B>REASONS FOR THE STUDY</B>

<P>While the market for laser systems has been extensively
analyzed in many market research reports, the materials and
components that comprise or are associated with lasers have
not been covered in great detail.  The market for laser
materials and components is highly stratified and competitive
and requires extensive analysis to fully understand.  

<P>The laser materials and components industry is undergoing
significant change.  Many of the markets that have
traditionally purchased these materials and components are
stagnant or declining, while other industries that have rarely
used components are showing increasing interest in employing
them.

<P>These changes are creating a market that is in flux for both
materials and component manufacturers and end users.  This
study attempts to identify the major industry movements and
trends and to serve as a guide for suppliers, manufacturers,
and users of this technology.<P>  


<B>CONTRIBUTION OF THE STUDY</B>

<P>Different sectors of the laser materials and components
industry will find this report beneficial in different ways. 
Manufacturers and suppliers of laser materials and components
will be able to identify those areas of the industry that are
in decline and those areas likely to experience strong growth. 
They will also be able to take advantage of new opportunities
identified in the report and alter their development and
marketing strategies accordingly.

<P>End users will be able to use the report to identify important
technological trends in instrumentation that will help them
use lasers more efficiently.  Other individuals will also find
this report valuable.  Technology specialists and venture
capitalists will gain an overview of this industry and will be
able to make informed decisions about where to direct
investments or development funding.  Engineers and researchers
will learn about important economic and technical trends
impacting their area of expertise.<P>


<B>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B>

<P>This report primarily focuses on the U.S. market for laser
materials and components.  However, Chapter 9 also provides an
overview of the international market.  The report is limited
to major classes of materials, components, instruments, and
equipment associated with lasers.  Coverage of smaller, highly
specialized areas has not been attempted.

<P>Most of this report is directed toward identifying and
analyzing market data and trends.  Chapters 4 through 8
analyze each major market segment in turn and form the heart
of the report.  Each of these chapters is organized as
follows:
<P>

<B>OVERVIEW</B>

<P>A brief summary of each market segment is presented first in
order to quickly orient the reader and facilitate quick
analysis.

<P>Products and Applications
<P>
The technology underlying each product is explained as are
major applications.<P>


<B>MARKET FORECASTS</B>

<P>Sales forecasts are presented for each product for the years
1995 to 2000, with an average annual growth rate calculated
for that period.  In addition, sales forecasts and average
annual growth rates are presented for each major application
area for the years 1995 to 2000. <P>


<B>MARKET SHARES</B>

<P>Market share estimates for each product category are estimated
for the year 1995.  Company background and product lines are
briefly discussed and analyzed.
Following Chapter 8 is an overview of the world market for
laser materials and components.  Chapter 10 comprises profiles
of 25 of the most important companies in the industry. 
Appendix A gives a complete listing of company names,
addresses, and phone numbers for each major company in the
industry.<P>


<B>METHODOLOGY</B>

<P>A careful methodology was followed to generate all the
forecasts contained in this report.  The methodology employed
both secondary sources of information and primary interviews
with a variety of industry participants to arrive at market
forecasts.

<P>First, sales figures for all material and component
manufacturers within each product category were gathered. 
When sales data was unavailable from published sources,
company managers and industry experts were consulted to arrive
at an accurate sales figure for each company.  For
manufacturers that produce components for more than one
product category, industry experts and company executives were
consulted to arrive at an estimate of what share of a
company's revenues should be assigned to each product.

<P>When sales figures were complete, they were added together to
estimate current market size for each product.  These data
were also used to estimate current market shares for all
companies.  The figures for current market size for each
product were reviewed by industry experts to ensure accuracy.

<P>Sales forecasts for each product were generated by analyzing
the growth of underlying industries that constitute demand for
each product.  First, the revenues generated by each end user
sector for each product were estimated based on published
sources or interviews with company marketing managers.  Then,
published data from numerous sources were used to forecast
growth in each end user sector through 2000.  This initial
estimate was adjusted up or down based on specific trends in
each application area and interviews with a variety of
industry sources.  

<P>A similar methodology was used to construct all the forecasts
and tables in the report.  Therefore, a separate methodology
explanation is not included in each chapter.

<P>A variety of information sources was used to compile this
study.  Some of the main sources include:

<UL><LI>    Detailed personal interviews with industry experts,
     including consultants, marketing managers,
       researchers, and executives of leading laser materials
       and components companies.  These interviews were used
       to obtain quantitative data as well as views on market
       and technological trends.
     
<LI>  Product literature, technical reports, and research
        papers from companies, universities, research
       institutes, and government agencies.
     
<LI>   Proceedings from the leading industry conferences,
        including the 1995 Conference on Lasers and Electro-
      Optics (CLEO) in Baltimore, MD.
   
<LI>     Various press reports on individual companies,
        technologies, and trends particularly from Laser Focus
     World, and Photonics-Spectra.
     
<LI>    Government publications including U.S. Industrial
        Outlook and other Department of Commerce studies.
<LI>      
<LI>        Publicly available company data from Dun & Bradstreet
         and Ward's Business Directory.</UL>

<P>
<B>AUTHOR'S CREDENTIALS</B>

<P>James Nicholson has been an industry analyst for the last six
years.  Mr. Nicholson is the Editor of NDT Update, a monthly
newsletter published by Quantum Publications, New York, NY. 
He also provides market consulting services for companies in
the laser, electro-optics, and inspection and measurement
fields.  This is his second report for BCC.

