<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
GB-187 FUTURE FOR OPTICAL COATINGS
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>GB-187 FUTURE FOR OPTICAL COATINGS
</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>JAMES NICHOLSON</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>


<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>


<B>STUDY GOAL AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

This study analyzes the market for optical coatings in the United States and abroad.  The 
study's primary goal is to give readers a clear understanding of where this market currently 
stands and where it is heading.  Detailed market forecasts are presented and important 
economic trends are analyzed to give readers a broad knowledge of the optical coatings 
area.  The basic technology involved in each of the product and service sectors is also 
explained in order to give readers a complete understanding of this complex and rapidly 
changing market.<P>  


<B>REASONS FOR THE STUDY</B><P>

The market for optical coatings and services has not been thoroughly analyzed for several 
years.  The market for optical coatings is highly stratified and competitive and requires 
extensive analysis to fully understand.<P>  

For the last several years, the optical coating industry has undergone significant change.  
New technological developments have made a variety of new coatings materials and 
deposition processes widely available for the first time.  The array of coatings and methods 
of depositing those coatings that are now available can be overwhelming, even to 
experienced industry professionals.  In the economic sphere, many coatings companies have 
had to wean themselves  away from a reliance on military applications and instead focus on 
fast changing and competitive commercial applications.<P>


These changes are creating a market that is in flux for both optical coatings manufacturers 
and service companies, as well as end users.  This study attempts to identify the major 
industry movements and trends and to serve as a guide for suppliers, manufacturers, and 
users of this technology.<P>  


<B>CONTRIBUTION OF THE STUDY</B><P>

Different sectors of the optical coatings industry will find this report beneficial in different 
ways.  Manufacturers and suppliers of optical coating materials and products will be able to 
identify those areas of the industry that are in decline and those areas likely to experience 
strong growth.  Likewise, optical coating service companies and deposition equipment 
vendors will  be able to take advantage of new opportunities identified in the report and alter 
their development and marketing strategies accordingly.<P>

End users will be able to use the report to identify important technological trends in coatings 
and deposition that will help them use optical coatings more efficiently.  Other individuals 
will also find this report valuable.  Technology specialists and venture capitalists will gain an 
overview of this industry and will be able to make informed decisions about where to direct 
investments or development funding.  Engineers and researchers will learn about important 
economic and technical trends impacting their area of expertise.<P>


<B>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B><P>

Wile this report primarily focuses on the U.S. market for optical coatings it also provides an 
overview of the international market.  The report is limited to major classes of materials, 
products, services, and equipment associated with optical coatings.  Coverage of smaller, 
highly specialized areas has not been attempted.<P>

Most of this report is directed toward identifying and analyzing market data and trends.  
Each major market segment is analyzed and is organized as follows:<P>

  Overview

          A brief summary of each market segment is presented first in order to orient 
the reader and facilitate quick analysis.<P>

  Products and Applications<P>

          The technology underlying each product is explained as are major 
applications.<P>



  Market Forecast

          Sales forecasts are presented for each product for the years 1995 to 2001, 
with an average annual growth rate calculated for the period of 1996 to 2001.  
In addition, sales forecasts and average annual growth rates are presented for 
each major application area for the years 1995 to 2001.<P>  



  Market Shares

          Market share estimates for each major market segment are estimated for the 
year 1996.  Company background and product lines are briefly discussed and 
analyzed.< P>

Two sections cover optical coating materials and services, respectively, and include an 
analysis of new coating materials and deposition processes.<P>

The following section presents an overview of the world market for laser materials and 
components. The final section comprises profiles of 15 of the most important companies in 
the industry.  Appendix A gives a complete listing of company names, addresses, and phone 
numbers for each major company in the industry.<P>


<B>METHODOLOGY</B><P>

A careful methodology was followed to generate all the forecasts contained in this report.  
The methodology employed both secondary sources of information and primary interviews 
with a variety of industry participants to arrive at market forecasts.<P>

First, sales figures for all major companies within each product category were gathered.  
When sales data was unavailable from published sources, company managers and industry 
experts were consulted to arrive at an accurate sales figure for each company.  For 
manufacturers that produce components for more than one product category, industry 
experts and company executives were consulted to arrive at an estimate of what share of a 
company's revenues should be assigned to each product.<P>

When sales figures were complete, they were added together to estimate current market 
size for each product.  This data was also used to estimate current market shares for all 
companies.  The figures for current market size for each product were reviewed by industry 
experts to ensure accuracy.<P>

Sales forecasts for each product were generated by analyzing the growth of underlying 
industries that constitute demand for each product.  First, the revenues generated by each 
end user sector for each product were estimated based on published sources or interviews 
with company marketing managers.  Then, published data from numerous sources was used 
to forecast growth in each end user sector through 2001.  This initial estimate was adjusted 
up or down based on specific trends in each application area and interviews with a variety 
of industry sources.<P>  

A similar methodology was used to construct all the forecasts and tables in the report.  
Therefore, a separate methodology explanation is not included in each chapter.<P>


<B>INFORMATION SOURCES</B><P>

A variety of information sources was used to compile this study.  Some of the main sources 
include:<P>
<UL>
    <LI> *  Detailed personal interviews with industry experts, including consultants, 
marketing managers, researchers, and executives of leading optical coating 
companies.  These interviews were used to obtain quantitative data as well as 
views on market and technological trends.<P>

    <LI> *    Product literature, technical reports, and research papers from companies, 
universities, research institutes, and government agencies.<P>

     <LI>*   Proceedings from the leading industry conferences, including the 1995 
Conference on Lasers and Electro-Optics (CLEO) in Baltimore, MD.<P>

     <LI>*    Various press reports on individual companies, technologies, and trends 
particularly from Laser Focus World,  Photonics-Spectra, and Applied Optics.<P>

     <LI>*    Government publications including U.S. Industrial Outlook and other 
Department of Commerce studies.<P>

     <LI>*    Publicly available company data from Dun & Bradstreet and Ward's Business 
Directory.<P>

</UL>
