levels.
  +Used both as barrier and structural resin
  #Includes only uses as a barrier resin for chemical packaging.
</PRE>

The selective barrier markets are in the healthcare area (for vapor
permeable Tyvek material) and in the controlled atmosphere
packaging area (CAP). The total market is currently estimated at
$72 million, and is expected to grow at 8% to $108 million by 1998.
The Tyvek market for healthcare packaging is mature, and whereas
the market for CAP films is evolving and expected to grow at a
robust 11% average annual rate over the next five years, as more
produce is centrally packaged and distributed in permeable films to
retain freshness for a longer time. The markets for selective
barrier films are summarized in Summary Table C.<P>


