<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>PLASTICS/ELASTOMERS UNDER-THE-HOOD: A ROBUST MARKET</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=Left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>P-123R PLASTICS/ELASTOMERS UNDER-THE-HOOD: A ROBUST MARKET</H2><HR><P>
<I>MEL SCHLECHTER</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>


<B>STUDY GOALS & OBJECTIVES</B>
<P>
The objective of this study is to provide a canvass of the
markets for plastics and rubber.  This involves determining the
size of the current market and also reviewing developmental
applications.</P>


<B>REASONS FOR DOING THE STUDY</B>
<P>
The primary reasons BCC conducted an under-the-hood parts study
was to clarify the many developments in the market of plastics
and rubber materials, and to establish a professional guide to
understanding the use of plastics and rubber in these kinds of
applications.</P>


<B>CONTRIBUTIONS OF THE STUDY</B>

<P>The present under-the-hood parts study is an accurate,
informative document for all those working in under-the-hood
applications.  Of particular value are the market statistics
presented in the study which should assist development, product
and market managers to understand the size and nature of the
market, both in plastics and rubber.</P>

<P>The report also provides research trends and data which will
assist the R&D community.

<P>It is especially valuable to companies which are already selling
to the under-the-hood market, and to those which want to market
new products.  Producers of most rubbers and a wide array of
plastics will find the report a valuable marketing tool.
</P>

<B>SCOPE & FORMAT</B>

<P>The report includes information on all under-the-hood rubber and
plastic products.  With rubbers, markets have been broken down
into hose and tubing, seals and gaskets, belting, wire and
cable, engine mounts and mechanical goods. Plastics are divided
into developmental and established uses.  Established uses such
as battery cases, ducting, reservoirs, fan shrouds and
electrical housings are covered.  In developmental applications,
the report includes throttle bodies, oil pans,  intake
manifolds, fuel rails and fuel system parts (such as fuel sender
modules and fuel line tubing).

<P>The report is presented in four sections.  Section I offers an
overview of the industry with definitions and key problems.
Overall statistics are also presented.  Section II encompasses
a review of rubber parts with separate market sections for each
of the applications mentioned above.  In Section III, plastic
and composite parts are described with a strong emphasis on
developmental plastics.  Finally, in Section IV, descriptions of
raw material and testing are presented in line with the
characteristics of the market.

<P>The report is based on both qualitative and quantitative market
research.  Approximately 150 primary research calls were made to
all quarters of the industry including elastomer and resin
suppliers, as well as molders and end-users.  An extensive
literature research also was conducted to produce a report with
both marketing and research information.
<P>

