<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
P-128  TOUGH PLASTICS:
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>P-128  TOUGH PLASTICS:</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>LARRY WANG<BR> JOSEPH MONGIELLO</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYSTS<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>GOALS AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

The objective of this study is an in-depth analysis of toughened
resin markets in automotive, industrial, construction, consumer,
medical and miscellaneous applications.<P>

The report analyzes four principal groups of toughened polymeric
materials; polyolefins, engineering resins and alloys, thermosets,
including matrix materials and intermediate-price resins. It notes
recent changes and developments in plastics toughening
technologies. The principal reasons for the expansion in the use of
toughened plastics are growing requirements for high-impact
resistant resins, needed to upgrade the presently used conventional
materials and the increased availability of toughened plastics due
to the improvements in copolymerization technology and in additive
impact-strength modification, as well as blending and alloying
methods.<P>

<B>Scope & Format</B><P>

This study is a thorough qualitative and quantitative analysis of
technology, markets and suppliers of different types of toughened
resins and impact modifiers. It also deals with the consumption
figures and five-year consumption forecasts for both specific
products and applications.<P>

<B>Methodology</B><P>

The report consists of five sections:<P>
<UL>1.      Overview<BR>
2.      Toughening Technologies<BR>
3.      Toughened Plastics-Major Groups<BR>
4.      Markets and Applications<BR>
5.      Suppliers of Toughened Resins and Systems</UL><P>

In the overview, major terms, such as toughened plastics, are
defined and the scope and limitations of the study are noted. Major
groups of toughened resins and research on toughening technologies
are broadly delineated, and reasons for the use of toughened
plastics, such as replacement of metals and non-metallic materials,
are discussed. Major properties required of toughened plastics are
identified. Industry structure as well as the overall consumption
patterns of toughened plastics are also listed.<P>

Section two on Toughening Technologies highlights new developments
and research work into toughening methods. The following topics are
discussed:<P>

<UL>1.
  New catalyst technology-control of molecular variables<BR>
2.
  Copolymerization, alloying and blending<BR>
3.
  Additive impact modifiers, mostly elastomers<BR>
4.
  Mechanism and toughening aspects<P></UL>

Impact modification technologies as related to specific resins and
systems are also discussed.<P>

Section three deals with different types of toughened
(impact-modified) resins and with different varieties of impact
modifiers. It provides information on properties, applications,
consumption figures and principal manufacturers of specific resins
and impact modifiers. Polyolefins, engineering resins and alloys,
thermosets, including matrix resins and intermediate-price resins
are discussed in detail. Elastomeric, rubber, polyacrylate,
polyethylene and polymeric plasticizers as impact modifiers are
discussed and their consumption is quantified.<P>

Section four deals with different markets for various types of
toughened resins. The principal applications are discussed within
each market and are quantified whenever possible. These markets
include: packaging, automotive, medical, industrial, consumer,
construction and miscellaneous uses.<P>

Finally, in the last section of the study, the principal suppliers
of particular toughened resin systems and their chief products are
discussed and are related to specific applications.<P>

<B>Contribution  & Target Audience</B><P>

This study is designed for manufacturers and users of toughened
polyolefins, engineering resins and alloys, thermosets,
intermediate-price resins and impact modifiers. It will assist them
in making sound decisions as far as markets, property requirements
for specific uses and potential sales levels of their products are
concerned. It will also provide them with information on
competitive products. Information included in this study will also
be useful to distributors of toughened plastics and impact
modifiers. It will also be of value to investment firms and market
analysts advising potential investors.<P>

<B>Information Sources</B><P>

Information sources for this study include interviews with many
representatives of manufacturers and consumers of toughened
plastics, technical and commercial magazines, private publications,
patents, papers presented at conferences and informal discussions
with their authors. Selected BCC Opportunity Reports have also been
used as a source of information. These include:<P>

<UL>P-015  Engineering Resins<BR>
     P-026  Thermoplastic Elastomers<BR>
     P-107 Medical Packaging<BR>
     P-075R  Optimization of Mechanical Properties of
Thermoplastics
                           Through Alloying<BR>
     P-053R  Transparent Plastics<BR>
     P-115  Processing and Impact Modification of Thermoplastics<BR>
     P-121  Plastics in Non-Packaging Medical Applications<P></UL>


