<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE> P-158 EXTRUDED PLASTICS: MARKETS, APPLICATIONS
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2> P-158 EXTRUDED PLASTICS: MARKETS, APPLICATIONS </H2>
<HR><P>
<I>HOWARD KIBBEL </I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>



<B>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B>

<P>This study is part of a continuing BCC series on the markets for plastics by type of
process used.  Extrusion accounts for the most plastics processed at more than
20 billion pounds annually or about one-third of the total plastics industry.  The
study discusses the major application areas for extruded products such as
pipe/conduit, wire/cable, film/sheet, hose/tubing, profiles, extrusion coatings
and extruded foam.  Virtually all of the thermoplastics are involved but the
emphasis is placed on the leading resins consumed -- the polyolefins, PVC and
polystyrene.  In addition to the description and data for each application and a
technology review, the major players in each application area are ranked by
sales.</P> 

<P>Data are reported for 1994, 1995 and 2000, with forecast growth rates for the
1995-2000 period.</P>

<B>METHODOLOGY</B>

<P>The research for this study included personal contacts with key participants
among the wide range of raw material suppliers, processors, and end users in all
of the major markets served by extrusion.  The information gathered from
primary sources formed the basis for our estimates of current plastics usage. 
Their comments on future demand were considered with supporting
macroeconomic data to evolve our 5-year forecasts.</P>

<P>In support of the primary research, we reviewed secondary sources of
information such as past BCC studies, the plastics trade publications, trade
associations, company literature and annual reports, industry conferences and
on-line databases.</P>


<B>RELATED BCC STUDIES</B>

<UL>
<LI>P-209R    Materials for Siding, Windows, Doors & Roofing    11/94

<LI>P-152     New Directions in Styrene-Based Plastics           10/94

<LI>P-043X    The Competitive Pipe Industry                     03/94

<LI>P-129     Plastics in Medical Tubing                        09/91

<LI>P-085N    What is New in Barrier Packaging for Food
          and Non-Food Products                             12/90
</UL>
</PRE> <BAR>



