<B>METHODOLOGY</B><P>

Research for this study consisted of extensive study of published literature, BCC
resources, and interviews with industrial, university and governmental sources.<P>

Published information was searched via databases covering medical, biological,
chemical and business fields. Additionally, dozens of books, government reports,
conference proceedings, company annual reports and related marketing reports were
consulted.<P>

Primary data collection was via interviews with industrial manufacturers, end users,
university and government experts, market watchers, and officials of governmental
and business associations.<P>

The information was discussed among the BCC staff and analyzed. The basis and
assumptions behind projected and forecasted markets are clearly defined in this
report.<P>


<B>BIOGRAPHY/QUALIFICATIONS</B><P>

Project analyst for this report, Dr. Yatin B. Thakore, has 12 years of industrial
experience in the areas of polymers, membranes and separation processes,
biomaterials, biotechnology, sensors, and in vitro diagnostics.<P>

Dr. Thakore obtained his doctorate degree from University of Utah, S.L.C., in
Materials Science and Engineering, with specialization in polymers and biomaterials.
He has his bachelor's degree in Chemical Engineering from Indian Institute of
Technology, Bombay, India.<P>

Dr. Thakore holds several U.S. and international patents for separation processes and
diagnostics.<P>


<B>RELATED BCC WORK</B><P>

The following reports published by BCC are related to this subject and are available
from BCC.<P>

